{{nihongo|'''Takayuki Ohira'''|<U+5927><U+5E73> <U+8CB4><U+4E4B>|<U+014C>hira Takayuki|born March 11, 1970}} is a Japanese engineer and the creator<ref>[http://www.make-digital.com/make/vol19/?pg=39, About Takayuki Ohira in Make Magazine] {{en icon}}</ref> of [[Megastar (projector)|Megastar]], a [[planetarium]] projector which was recorded in [[Guinness World Records]]<ref>[http://www.miraikan.jst.go.jp/sp/megastar2cosmos/index_e.html, Japan National museum of emerging science and innovation]{{en icon}}</ref> as the planetarium projector that can project the most number of stars in the world.

== Profile ==
Ohira was born in [[Kawasaki, Kanagawa]] on March 11, 1970, and graduated from faculty of mechanical engineering and graduate school of precision engineering in [[Nihon University]].<ref>[http://www.megastar.jp/en/creator/index.php About creator, Megastar official website] {{en icon}}
</ref>

